SIMPLE: extrude
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Extrude
<hw>Ex*trude"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Extruded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Extruding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>extrudere</ets>,
<ets>extrusum</ets>; <ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>trudere</ets> to thrust,
akin to E. <ets>threat</ets>. See <er>Threat</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To thrust out; to force, press, or push out; to expel; to drive off
or away.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Parentheses thrown into notes or
<xex>extruded</xex> to the margin.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Metallurgy)</fld> <def>To shape or form by forcing
metal heated to a semi-plastic condition through dies by the use of
hydraulic power; <as>as, <ex>extruded</ex> metal, <ex>extruded</ex>
rods, <ex>extruded</ex> shapes</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extrusion</ent>⟦br⟧
